00:50:49,280 --> 00:50:58,280
 So in the 80s, 87 London, for example, Big Bang, then also in the US in the 90s, the financial sector really expanded rapidly.

422
00:50:58,280 --> 00:51:01,280
 And of course, there was a lot of deregulation, which was one big reason.

423
00:51:01,280 --> 00:51:11,280
 But maybe also because inflation targeting ultimately achieved its goal of stable inflation that also enabled long term financial contracting.

