00:51:42,280 --> 00:51:47,280
 There is this whole literature now about the risk taking channel of monetary policy,

431
00:51:47,280 --> 00:51:58,280
 basically explaining how in the run up to 2008, to the 2008 crisis, low interest rates basically fostered or fueled banks

432
00:51:58,280 --> 00:52:07,280
 to take more risk, lend to riskier borrowers, lend bigger, and take more leverage, this kind of chase for yield.

433
00:52:07,280 --> 00:52:16,280
 And the other thing that I still remember, I'm not as old as you as Claudio, of course, but I do still remember that in the early...

434
00:52:16,280 --> 00:52:22,280
 Oh, yeah, no, it doesn't look like, I look like as old as him, but I'm not, okay.

435
00:52:22,280 --> 00:52:31,280
 I still remember that when in the early 2000s, when The Economist every year, the magazine The Economist every year predicted the financial crisis in the US,

